📄 Student Performance Analysis Report
🟦 1. Introduction

In today’s data-driven world, analyzing student performance helps educators understand learning patterns and improve teaching strategies. This project focuses on analyzing a dataset of student scores to identify key factors affecting academic performance.

The analysis uses Python-based data science tools to explore relationships between variables such as gender, lunch type, and test preparation.

🟦 2. Dataset Description

The dataset contains 1000 student records with the following features:

Gender
Race/Ethnicity
Parental Level of Education
Lunch Type
Test Preparation Course
Math Score
Reading Score
Writing Score

A new feature called average_score was created to represent overall student performance.

🟦 3. Objectives

The main objectives of this project are:

Analyze student performance across subjects
Identify factors affecting performance
Compare performance across categories
Visualize data using charts
Generate meaningful insights
