🟦 8. Conclusion

The analysis shows that student performance is influenced by multiple factors such as gender, socio-economic conditions, and preparation level. Mathematics appears to be the weakest subject, while reading and writing show stronger performance.

The findings suggest that targeted interventions, such as additional math support and encouraging test preparation, can improve overall student outcomes.
